124 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENT PAPERBACKS: A BACKWARD PLACE BY RUTH PRAWER JHABVALA (FIRESIDE: $7.95) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In this delightful comedy of manners, Ruth Jhabvala uses the story of three 
English expatriates in Delhi to examine the changing role of women in a society 
divided between liberal, imported British values and traditional, paternalistic 
Indian mores. 
</P>
<P>
Clarissa's patronizing efforts to "go native" in grubby peasant costumes 
embarrass her friends; brittle, blond Etta places so much emphasis on her 
European sophistication that she becomes a self-caricature. Inspired by the 
love of her impractical Indian husband, sensible, level-headed Judy learns to 
reconcile seemingly inimical traditions into an agreeable way of life. Rising 
above her compatriots, she demonstrates the superiority of spiritual resources 
to mere creature comforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
