<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRACING THE DIRECTIONS OF GAY THEATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ray Loynd's Jan. 7 article asks where does gay theater go from here. The answer 
is: In all directions, because of its diversity. 
</P>
<P>
Gay theater is liberating for all involved. It creates a supportive community 
for talented gay and lesbian playwrights, performers and theater folk and 
straights who share our dreams. 
</P>
<P>
Gay theater is where a 50-year-old lesbian can see two women embrace on stage 
for the first exciting time. It is survival, anger, spirit, gentleness, magic 
and love. 
</P>
<P>
It will be necessary until my lover and I can walk arm-in-arm down any street 
in Los Angeles without fear. 
</P>
<P>
BILL KAISER, The Purple Circuit Hotline, Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 The Purple Circuit Hotline is a public-information service for gay and lesbian 
plays. 
</P>
<P>
