<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: HI-TECH; 
</P>
<P>
EVERYTHING BUT THE KITCHEN CALCULATOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBARA THORNBURG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANYONE WHO HAS EVER forgotten in mid-recipe how many tablespoons make a quarter 
of a cup will appreciate the Kitchen Whiz recipe-conversion calculator by Seiko 
Instruments. 
</P>
<P>
It also enlarges or reduces recipes and converts European metric recipes to 
U.S. weights and measures. 
</P>
<P>
Based on a Massachusetts Institute of Technology patent, the Kitchen Whiz 
computes cooking times for roasts and acts as a food-preparation timer, 
temperature converter, clock, calendar and calculator. Powered with two AA 
batteries, it comes with a full one-year warranty and sells for $59.95. 
Available at major department stores. BARBARA THORNBURG 
</P>
</TEXT>
