SCHOOL GETS GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The School of Theology at Azusa Pacific University has been awarded a $2,500 
grant from Lilly Endowment Inc. to strengthen its governing board. 
</P>
<P>
The school is one of 40 North American institutions selected for the $791,000 
grant program by the Indianapolis-based charitable foundation, which supports 
religious institutions and nonprofit leadership. 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific is an inter-denominational Christian college with 3,000 students 
that offers 30 undergraduate majors, 12 master's programs and one doctoral 
program. 
</P>
