<P>
BOYCOTT SOUTH AFRICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was keenly disappointed to see the headline, "Native Crafts Are Reason for 
South African Visit," (Dec. 24). There is no good reason for a South Africa 
visit in today's political climate, and Times staff writer Norman Dash has 
shown a lack of sensitivity to the struggle against apartheid by giving such 
prominent display to a trip which is being boycotted by all those who oppose 
this racist regime. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM G. SMITH 
</P>
<P>
Lawyers Against Apartheid 
</P>
