</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Electric Co. will detail next week in Cincinnati plans to develop what 
is billed as the world's biggest and most powerful civilian jet engine, 
designed to power the new generation of jumbo jets in the next century, a 
company spokesman said. The engine will permit the proposed Boeing 777 super 
jumbo jet and other planes to handle increased weight with only two engines 
rather than the three or four on today's jets, saving fuel costs and providing 
greater operating efficiency, the spokesman said. Sources said the impetus for 
the new engine was the recent announcement by Boeing Co. that it would go ahead 
with plans to build its 777. 
