WEST COAST CONFERENCE; 
</P>
<P>
PORTLAND ENDS ST. MARY'S STREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Portland used an 11-0 run with 10 minutes left to take control and the Pilots 
went on to beat St. Mary's, 58-46, Saturday night in a West Coast Conference 
game at Portland, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Spoelstra led the Pilots (4-11, 1-1) with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
The loss snapped a four-game win streak for the Gaels (5-10, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
Gonzaga 63, USF 62 -- Brian Frederickson scored with 1:18 remaining to give the 
Bulldogs (6-9, 1-1) the lead for good at Spokane, Wash. The Dons are 5-11 and 
1-2. 
</P>
