<P>
BRIEFING / EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Costa Mesa City Council will be asked at its meeting Monday to delay the 
eviction of the Share Our Selves charity from the Rea Community Center. 
</P>
<P>
Directors from SOS will ask the council to put off the ouster until the charity 
can buy and remodel a new headquarters. The council can either order the 
charity's eviction effective Tuesday, grant the directors' request or come up 
with an alternative plan. The meeting begins at 6:30 p.m. in the council 
chambers at Costa Mesa City Hall, 77 Fair Drive. 
</P>
