<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PALMISANO SCORES 36 IN THOUSAND OAKS LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After her standout freshman season of 1989, much was expected of Thousand Oaks 
High guard Michelle Palmisano. And while she has delivered, sometimes it still 
has not been enough. 
</P>
<P>
In a Marmonte League game at Thousand Oaks on Saturday night, Palmisano scored 
a game-high 36 points, but the Lancers nonetheless lost to Westlake, 63-58. 
</P>
<P>
Forward Melissa Gische had 25 points to lead a trio of double-figure scorers 
for Westlake (4-0 in league play). 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks is 8-9, 1-3. 
</P>
<P>
In other girls' games: 
</P>
<P>
Village Christian 53, Miraleste 31 -- Forward Jana Kovar scored 14 points in 
the first half, three more than the Miraleste team, and host Village Christian 
(7-4, 4-0) rolled in the Alpha League game. 
</P>
<P>
Kovar finished with 22 points and 17 rebounds. Center LeeAnn Robinson had 18 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Brentwood 62, Campbell Hall 52 -- Despite 19 points and 21 rebounds by Kirsten 
Williams, Campbell Hall (6-6, 1-2) fell in a Delphic League game at home. 
Joanna Paul added 10 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Highland Hall 43, Cedu 11 -- Highland Hall (6-5) climbed above .500 for the 
first time in seven years at Stonehurst Park in Sun Valley. Monica Palma scored 
a game-high 12 points and added 12 rebounds for the Hawks. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS 
</P>
<P>
L. A. Baptist 52, Maranatha 46 -- Alex Pistone scored 12 points and had 14 
rebounds as L. A. Baptist, which trailed, 43-38, buried Maranatha with a 14-2 
run to open the fourth quarter in an Alpha League game at L. A. Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
Dan Shackelford added 15 points for L. A. Baptist (2-2 in league play). 
</P>
