<HEADLINE>
<P>
PARKS CONSERVATION EXECUTIVE APPOINTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peter Ireland, a former aide to Los Angeles County Supervisor Deane Dana, has 
been appointed assistant executive officer of the Mountains Recreation and 
Conservation Authority. 
</P>
<P>
The authority, based in Malibu, is responsible for operations and park 
development on lands acquired by the Santa Monica Mountains Conservancy. The 
conservancy's executive director, Joe Edmiston, serves as the authority's ex 
officio executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
Edmiston said that Ireland's appointment brings "an added dimension of 
management ability at a time when it is especially critical that we work more 
closely with county government and citizens groups." 
</P>
</TEXT>
